<history>
<p>Since its introduction in 3126, the Gurzil has seen service primarily within Clan Jade Falcon's second-line and garrison forces, where its fire support capabilities complement frontline OmniMech formations. The tank found its niche in defensive operations and siege warfare, where commanders could position Gurzils to maximize their range-optimized targeting system's effectiveness.</p>

<p>The Dark Age conflicts provided numerous opportunities for the Gurzil to demonstrate its capabilities. In 3140, during defensive operations on Chahar, Falcon forces employed Gurzils in urban warfare scenarios with notable success. Working in coordination with Elemental spotters, tank crews leveraged the mortars' indirect fire capability to strike targets concealed behind buildings while using the Streak launchers against enemies in direct line of sight. This combined-arms approach proved effective during a weeklong siege, repelling multiple Lyran Commonwealth Armed Forces sorties.</p>

<p>The 3142 invasion of Arcturus by Peregrine Galaxy showcased the Gurzil in a more conventional role. During the Battle of Warnemünde, two Points of Gurzils were deployed to hold the Stein Garten bridge against the Fifteenth Arcturan Guards. Positioned in reserve across the river from the main Falcon line, the tanks remained outside the initial engagement. When Lyran forces pushed across the bridgehead, they found themselves squarely within the Gurzils' optimal engagement envelope. Concentrated volleys of LRM and mortar fire halted the Lyran advance within minutes. Subsequent attempts to flank the position or ford the river met similar fates, with the Gurzils' overlapping fields of fire proving devastating against the already-damaged Guard 'Mechs. The engagement demonstrated that while the Gurzil may struggle in fluid, maneuver-based combat, it excels when employed in prepared defensive positions where its range-optimized systems can be fully exploited.</p>
</history>

